.TH rpc.rwalld 8
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lrpc.rwalld\*O, \*Lrwalld\*O \- Network rwall server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*L/usr/etc/rpc.rwalld\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX  "rwalld command"
.iX  "network rwall server" "rwalld"
.IX  "servers" "rwalld"
.PP
The \*Lrwalld\*O is a server that handles \*Lrwall\*O(1) and \*Lshutdown\*O(2)
requests.  It is implemented by calling \*Lwall\*O(1)
to all the appropriate network machines.
The \*Lrwalld\*O daemon is normally invoked by \*Linetd\*O(8) by removing the
comment character (#) at the beginning of the \*Lrwalld\*O entry in the
\*L/etc/inetd.conf\*O file.
.SH "RELATED INFORMATION"
.PP
Commands: \*Lrwall\*O (1C),
\*Lwall\*O (1),
\*Lshutdown\*O (2)
\*Lservices\*O (5)
.PP
Daemons: \*Linetd\*O (8)
